120/* default i/o buffer size -- double this for output when reading (this and
121 twice this must be able to fit in an unsigned type) */
122#define GZBUFSIZE 8192

124/* gzip modes, also provide a little integrity check on the passed structure */
125#define GZ_NONE 0
126#define GZ_READ 7247
127#define GZ_WRITE 31153
128#define GZ_APPEND 1 /* mode set to GZ_WRITE after the file is opened */
129
130/* values for gz_state how */
131#define LOOK 0 /* look for a gzip header */
132#define COPY 1 /* copy input directly */
133#define GZIP 2 /* decompress a gzip stream */
134
135/* internal gzip file state data structure */
136typedef struct {
137 /* exposed contents for gzgetc() macro */
138 struct gzFile_s x; /* "x" for exposed */
139 /* x.have: number of bytes available at x.next */
140 /* x.next: next output data to deliver or write */
141 /* x.pos: current position in uncompressed data */
142 /* used for both reading and writing */
143 int mode; /* see gzip modes above */
144 int fd; /* file descriptor */
145 char *path; /* path or fd for error messages */
146 unsigned size; /* buffer size, zero if not allocated yet */
147 unsigned want; /* requested buffer size, default is GZBUFSIZE */
148 unsigned char *in; /* input buffer */
149 unsigned char *out; /* output buffer (double-sized when reading) */
150 int direct; /* 0 if processing gzip, 1 if transparent */
151 /* just for reading */
152 int how; /* 0: get header, 1: copy, 2: decompress */
153 z_off64_t start; /* where the gzip data started, for rewinding */
154 int eof; /* true if end of input file reached */
155 int past; /* true if read requested past end */
156 /* just for writing */
157 int level; /* compression level */
158 int strategy; /* compression strategy */
159 /* seek request */
160 z_off64_t skip; /* amount to skip (already rewound if backwards) */
161 int seek; /* true if seek request pending */
162 /* error information */
163 int err; /* error code */
164 char *msg; /* error message */
165 /* zlib inflate or deflate stream */
166 z_stream strm; /* stream structure in-place (not a pointer) */
167} gz_state;
168typedef gz_state FAR *gz_statep;
169
170/* shared functions */
171void ZLIB_INTERNAL gz_error OF((gz_statep, int, const char *));
172#if defined UNDER_CE
173char ZLIB_INTERNAL *gz_strwinerror OF((DWORD error));
174#endif

176/* GT_OFF(x), where x is an unsigned value, is true if x > maximum z_off64_t
177 value -- needed when comparing unsigned to z_off64_t, which is signed
178 (possible z_off64_t types off_t, off64_t, and long are all signed) */
179#ifdef INT_MAX
180# define GT_OFF(x) (sizeof(int) == sizeof(z_off64_t) && (x) > INT_MAX)
181#else
182unsigned ZLIB_INTERNAL gz_intmax OF((void));
183# define GT_OFF(x) (sizeof(int) == sizeof(z_off64_t) && (x) > gz_intmax())
184#endif
